# AI Test Generation Platform — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Web platform that parses backend codebases (Laravel/FastAPI/Spring Boot),
generates API test cases using Gemini AI, executes them via Newman,
and produces structured bug reports.

## Backend Stack
- FastAPI (Python 3.11) — async throughout
- PostgreSQL + SQLAlchemy (async) + Alembic migrations
- Celery + Redis for async task queue
- Gemini Flash as primary LLM, Claude Sonnet as fallback
- Newman CLI for test execution

## Frontend Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript
- TailwindCSS + ShadCN UI
- Zustand for global state
- Axios for API calls (always through lib/api.ts)
- WebSocket for live execution streaming

## Critical Rules
- All parsers output standard EndpointMap JSON (see parsers/base.py)
- All AI prompts live in app/ai/prompts.py — never inline elsewhere
- All DB calls must be async (use async with AsyncSession)
- All endpoints validated with Pydantic schemas
- Never commit .env files — use .env.example as template
- Supported frameworks: laravel, fastapi, spring_boot only

## Folder Structure
backend/app/
  models/     — SQLAlchemy ORM models
  schemas/    — Pydantic request/response schemas
  routers/    — FastAPI route handlers
  parsers/    — Framework-specific codebase parsers
  ai/         — LLM integration and prompts
  execution/  — Newman runner and collection builder
  tasks/      — Celery async tasks
  services/   — Business logic
  websocket/  — WebSocket handlers

## API Base URL
Development: http://localhost:8000
All endpoints prefixed with /v1
